Box Office Bomb Budget 90 million without PA costs 205 million with 115 million in PA Box office 26985835 domestic so far 65485835 worldwide so far Tom Hoopers starstudded adaptation of the iconic Andrew Lloyd Webber musical was doomed the moment its first trailer dropped and turned into Snark Bait overnight thanks to its digital fur technology turning the cast into bizarre CGI cathumanhybrids The film was Christmas Rushed to such an extent that it initially shipped with several unfinished effects leading Universal and Hooper in an unprecedented move to issue new prints to fix them just a couple days after its release It still wasnt enough to save Cats which was already declawed by the doubleedged sword of critics tearing it apart and the family crowd being alienated by the aforementioned cat designs and the films current of sexuality despite the PG rating resulting in it making only 66 million on opening weekend  one of the worst opening weekends in box office history for a widerelease film Opening the same day as the muchhyped Star Wars The Rise of Skywalker certainly didnt help as well as facing strong runs from Jumanji The Next Level and Frozen II While Universal was confident the film could overcome this weak start and pull in big holiday numbers similar to The Greatest Showman another musical that opened against the previous Star Wars episode Cats lacked the audience enthusiasm that Greatest Showman had and experienced huge dropoffs going from 3380 theaters to just 146 theaters within a month of its debut
